DEFINITION: Any kind of street or way
Highest-performance highway within a territory that deserve main towns. Usually have a reglemented access
Important high-performance highway that are not motorways. Deserving main towns
Important highway linking large towns. Usually have two lanes but not separeted by a central barrier
Highway linking large towns. Usually have two lanes but not separeted by a central barrier
Highway linking small settlements, or the local centres of a large town or city
Highway generally used for local traffic within settlement. Usually highway accesing or around residential areas

Minor public highway typically at the lowest level of the interconnecting grid network. Have lower importance in the highway network than tertiary and are not residential streets or agricultural tracks
Roads for mostly agricultural use, forest tracks etc.; usually unpaved (unsealed) but may apply to paved tracks as well, that are suitable for two-track vehicles, such as tractors or jeeps
A generic multi-use path open to non-motorized vehicles
For designated footpaths, i.e. mainly/exclusively for pedestrians
Separated way for the use of cyclists
For flights of steps on footways and paths
Generally a circular (self-intersecting) highway junction where the traffic on the roundabout has right of way
A ferry route used to transport things or people from one bank of a watercourse or inlet to the other, or as a permanent or seasonal local maritime link, and a link to a foreign country
